oting payment story\u2014offer bank-file-only solution (acceptable per Heinrich 2026-01-08: 'the solution creates a payment file') OR propose alternative Zycus payment-partner options (compile list from Zycus partner network and send to MFAM within 7 days). Re-anchor value on AP automation + Merlin AI (the demo strengths) and treat payment as modular add-on, not core dependency.", "threat_level": "high", "last_confirmed": "2026-07-07T05:59:38.450750+05:30"}]}, "champion_strength": {"source": "Avoma calls 8 Jan 2026 and 8 May 2026; SF Next_Step__c 19 Jun 2026", "at_risk": true, "summary": "Heinrich Zaguirre has done real legwork (compiling AP requirements, organizing the demo, pulling in three new stakeholders) but has shown no advocacy against rivals and is the sole active thread, which has already stalled the deal once during his vacation.", "champion": "Heinrich Zaguirre", "strength": "developing"}, "stakeholder_map": {"items": [{"name": "Anthony Fonzo", "risk": "Not developed as a champion; no post-demo follow-up logged", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "adifonzo@mfamc.org", "title": "Director, Finance & Operations", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "engaged, neutral", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-05-08"}, {"name": "Shifa Garewal", "role": "Evaluator", "email": "sgarewal@mfamc.org", "title": "Information Technology Analyst", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "_role_inferred": true}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma call 8 Jan 2026 (Heinrich Zaguirre)"], "narrative": "The buyer never quantified savings or ROI; the articulated pain is qualitative: fully manual PDF-based vendor onboarding stored in SharePoint, ~100 vendors, and manual invoice review culminating in COO sign-off, all described by Heinrich Zaguirre on the 8 Jan 2026 discovery call. The only numbers exchanged were Zycus's own pricing ($80K-150K annual licensing, roughly a 1:1 implementation fee), which Heinrich said 'wouldn't be the number one driving factor' but would still be scrutinized by the AP team. No customer-side cost-of-inaction figure has been surfaced."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma call 8 Jan 2026 (Heinrich Zaguirre)", "SF Next_Step__c, 19 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "Heinrich Zaguirre has done real internal legwork - he pulled together requirements, compiled and forwarded AP-team questions ahead of the demo, and organized the wider team (Anthony Fonzo, Denni Wong, Jasmine Shen) for the 8 May 2026 session. That is developing champion behavior. Set against it: he explicitly refused to name competitors 'to be fair to the AP guys' rather than help Zycus win, and he is the sole active thread - his vacation as of 19 Jun 2026 stalled the entire deal with no one covering for him. Engagement is currently cooling, not advancing."}, "competition": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma call 8 Jan 2026 (Heinrich Zaguirre)", "SF Competitors__c", "SF Next_Step__c, 26 Jun 2026"], "narrative": "No competitor has been confirmed active by direct buyer evidence. Heinrich declined on 8 Jan 2026 to name rivals but confirmed MFAM is evaluating both Gartner Magic Quadrant leaders and smaller-scale platforms - consistent with the eight names logged in Competitors__c (Coupa, Oracle, SAP Ariba, GEP Worldwide, iValua, JAGGAER, Workday, Ironclad), none of which has surfaced by name in either matched call. The real live threat to this deal is not a rival vendor but TransferMate, Zycus's own payment-execution partner, whose slow, rocky demo/pricing follow-through (8 May-26 Jun 2026) is souring the buyer against the whole Zycus proposal. The wedge that is landing is the Merlin/Teams chatbot, which Heinrich called unique in the space."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma call 8 Jan 2026 (Heinrich Zaguirre)", "Avoma call 8 May 2026 (Denni Wong)"], "narrative": "Pain is well documented and specific: Heinrich Zaguirre described vendor onboarding as fully manual (PDF form